<br>
Say doesn't seem to work for language learning, and even if it did, you might annoy the people around you.  Use /g.  Also turn /g off in the chat filters menu (you don't see the spam on your screen bu you still get the skill increases) and use /serverfilter on so that the spam isn't geting pushed across the Internet just to be ignored.<br>
<br>
Make sure the person you are working with knows that you are ignoring /g, so they will use /say or /tell to communicate with you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukisarintenamin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KisarinTenamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 9:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some classes ..</span><hr size=1> I have found a new EXCELLENT place to work on languages that is safe for all races: the zone between the Nexus and the Bazaar on Luclin. I timed the zones and it was 12 seconds max both ways. I am not sure that I could do that even in Felwithe. and it is safe for all characters.<br>
